To configure Decision Center (DC) to use the SSP deployed on a different application server, you can leverage the IlrSSPResolver interface.

Here are the steps to follow:

1. **Implement a custom SSP Resolver**: Create a Java class that implements the `IlrSSPResolver` interface. This class will be responsible for determining the correct SSP URL based on the server name specified in the Decision Center configuration.

```java
public class CustomSSPResolver implements IlrSSPResolver {
    @Override
    public URL getSSPURL(String serverName, URL url) {
        // Implement the logic to determine the correct SSP URL based on the server name
        if (serverName.equals("runtimeServer")) {
            try {
                return new URL("http://runtimeServerHost:9000/testing");
            } catch (MalformedURLException e) {
                throw new RuntimeException("Error creating SSP URL", e);
            }
        } else {
            // Return the default SSP URL if the server name doesn't match
            return url;
        }
    }
}
```

2. **Package the custom SSP Resolver**: Package the `CustomSSPResolver` class in a JAR file and include it in the `WEB-INF/lib` directory of the `teamserver.war` file.

3. **Configure the SSP Resolver in Decision Center**: In the Decision Center configuration, set the `teamserver.defaultSSPResolver.class` property to the fully qualified name of the custom SSP Resolver class (e.g., `com.example.CustomSSPResolver`).

   - For WebSphere Application Server, you can set this property in the `WEB-INF/web.xml` file of the `teamserver.war` file:

   ```xml
   <context-param>
       <param-name>teamserver.defaultSSPResolver.class</param-name>
       <param-value>com.example.CustomSSPResolver</param-value>
   </context-param>
   ```

   - For other application servers, refer to the documentation on how to set custom application properties.

4. **Deploy the Decision Center and Runtime Server**: Deploy the Decision Center (with the custom SSP Resolver) on the management server and the Runtime Server (with the XU, SSP, and RES) on the separate application server.

Now, when you run DVS tests from Decision Center, the custom `IlrSSPResolver` implementation will be used to determine the correct SSP URL based on the server name specified in the Decision Center configuration. The tests will be executed on the SSP deployed on the runtime server (at `http://runtimeServerHost:9000/testing`), instead of the management server where the RES console is deployed.

This approach allows you to have a clear separation between the management and runtime components, and ensures that the DVS tests are executed on the correct SSP deployment.

